      "body": "<!--e57a25ab6845829454e8d69fc972939a-->\n\nThe following sections might be updated with supplementary metadata relevant to reviewers and maintainers.\n\n<!--021abf342d371248e50ceaed478a90ca-->\n### Reviews\nSee [the guideline](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#code-review) for information on the review process.\n| Type | Reviewers |\n| ---- | --------- |\n| Concept ACK | [hebasto](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/34623#issuecomment-3927779755) |\n\nIf your review is incorrectly listed, please copy-paste <code>&lt;!--meta-tag:bot-skip--&gt;</code> into the comment that the bot should ignore.\n<!--5faf32d7da4f0f540f40219e4f7537a3-->\n### LLM Linter (✨ experimental)\n\n\n\nPossible places where comparison-specific test macros should replace generic comparisons:\n\n- src/secp256k1/src/modules/ellswift/tests_impl.h\n  +    CHECK(secp256k1_ellswift_xdh(CTX, output, ell_a64, ell_b64, s_zero, 0, &ellswift_xdh_hash_x32, NULL) == 0);\n  +    CHECK(secp256k1_ellswift_xdh(CTX, output, ell_a64, ell_b64, secp256k1_group_order_bytes, 0, &ellswift_xdh_hash_x32, NULL) == 0);\n  +    CHECK(secp256k1_ellswift_xdh(CTX, output, ell_a64, ell_b64, s_overflow_plus1, 0, &ellswift_xdh_hash_x32, NULL) == 0);\n  +    CHECK(secp256k1_ellswift_xdh(CTX, output, ell_a64, ell_b64, s_overflow_minus1, 0, &ellswift_xdh_hash_x32, NULL) == 1);\n  -> Recommendation: replace generic CHECK(expr == const) uses with a comparison-specific test helper (for example CHECK_EQUAL(expected, actual) or a project-appropriate macro) so failures report expected vs actual clearly instead of a generic boolean failure.\n\n- src/secp256k1/src/tests.c\n  +    CHECK(secp256k1_scalar_check_overflow(&s) == 0);\n  +    CHECK(secp256k1_scalar_check_overflow(&n_minus_1) == 0);\n  +    CHECK(secp256k1_scalar_check_overflow(&n) == 1);\n  +    CHECK(secp256k1_scalar_check_overflow(&n_plus_1) == 1);\n  +    CHECK(secp256k1_scalar_check_overflow(&max) == 1);\n  ...\n  +        expected_overflow = (secp256k1_memcmp_var(b32, secp256k1_group_order_bytes, 32) >= 0);\n  ...\n  +        secp256k1_scalar_set_b32(&s, b32, &overflow);\n  +        CHECK(overflow == expected_overflow);\n  -> Recommendation: use comparison-specific test helpers (e.g., CHECK_EQUAL(expected, actual) or equivalent) instead of CHECK(expr == value). This gives clearer failure messages (expected vs actual) and improves test diagnostics.\n\nIf your test framework provides a specific macro for equality/inequality (or numeric comparisons), prefer that instead of checking boolean expressions with CHECK(... == ...). If no such macro exists in the project, consider adding one to improve the clarity of test failures.\n\n\n\n<sup>2026-02-24 10:04:07</sup>\n",
